view.name: Farmers Markets in New York State
view.attribution: New York State Department of Agriculture and Markets
view.description: In the past decade the number of farmers markets in New York State has grown at a rapid rate.  The dataset contains information detailing the time and location of community farmers markets as well as the name and phone number of the market manager.

columns.name: County
columns.description: County the Farmers’ Market is located in

columns.name: Location
columns.description: General place or common name of the location where the market is set up

columns.name: Operating Months
columns.description:
P=Spring(operating in April or May)
M=Summer(operating in June, July, Aug, Sept, Oct, Nov)
X=Extended Season(operating in Dec)
W=Winter(operating in Jan, Feb, March)
YR=Year-round(continually operating at the same location all year long)

columns.name: FMNP
columns.description: Y: Market is part of the WIC/Senior Farmers Market Nutrition Program

columns.name: EBT/SNAP
columns.description: Y=Market supports EBT/SNAP; EBT- Electronic Benefit Transfer, SNAP-Supplemental Nutrition Assistance Program

columns.name: FCC Issued
columns.description: Y indicates the market is issuing one $2.00 FreshConnect Check for every $5.00 in SNAP EBT transaction.

columns.name: FCC Accepted
columns.description: Y indicates the market is accepting $2.00 FreshConnect Checks from customers as payment for eligible food items; customers should not assume checks are also being issued at these locations, as this may or may not be the case.

Dataset Summary.Dataset Owner: New York State Department of Agriculture and Markets

Notes.Notes: Database contains information on approximately 500 community farmers markets located throughout the State.  The data is updated weekly and as we become aware of new markets and updates to existing markets.  Along with the time and location of the market, the name and phone number of the market manager are provided to allow customers and farmers to contact the market directly to get up to the day information on the operations of the market.
